EDGY FOUR! Just the two slips in play but don't think that would have carried! Fuller and around off, Rahul looks to drive, this one goes off the outside edge, past the diving second slip fielder and into the third man fence again. England's frustration continues.
Invites him to drive yet again with a full one outside off, Rahul this time lets it be.
Now goes full and looks to hit the front pad of Rahul! He gets his bat down in time and works it to mid-wicket.
Gets off strike as he pushes it towards mid off.
A dot to end! On off, it is blocked nicely.
Fuller and on off, Rahul strokes it to covers.
Length and around off, angles away. Rahul plays inside the line and lets it be.
Well left again! On off, watches it closely as it angles away. Leaves it alone.
Plays it late now and angles it down to third man for one.
Singles coming easily now! Fuller and on off, Sharma pushes it towards mid off for one.
Slightly shorter and on the pads, tucking the batter for room. It is worked to mid-wicket.
Angled into middle, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
BEATEN AGAIN! Length and on off, this lands, takes off and holds its line. Rahul looks to block but is beaten.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Uppish but wide of the fielder! Outside off, Rahul does go after it, it goes more off the outer half past backward point and down to the third man fence.
Outside off, Rahul goes back to leaving it.
Another one outside off, Rahul does not fiddle with it again.
FOUR! Runs flowing now! Really full and outside off, Sharma says thank you very much and strokes it through cover-point.
FOUR BYES! Bonus runs now! Trail under 100! Down the leg side, swings away further. Rohit misses the flick, Buttler has no chance at all and it goes down to the fine leg fence.
Another extra! England are probably just trying a little too much! On middle, it is kept out. Curran has overstepped.
Bowls a yorker now on off, Sharma jams it out.
Shorter and on the body, Sharma nudges it down to fine leg and takes one.
BEAUTY! Almost unplayable! This starts on off, threatens to come back in but then pitches and moves away. Rahul is beaten as he tries to block.
Back of a length and on middle, Rahul defends it nicely.
Slips this one down the leg side. Sharma looks to flick but misses.
Good length and on middle, Sharma stands tall and plays it onto the ground.
Good length and on off, Sharma plays it nice and late and towards gully.
A big inswinger! Banana swing but this starts from just outside off. Rohit misses his flick and is hit on the pads. Clearly going down leg.
Once again gets it to come back in but the line is a little too straight. Rahul looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and rolls on the leg side. A leg bye taken.
A harmless nut to end! Outside off, left alone.
BEATEN! Frustrating for England again! On a length and around off, this lands and then moves away. Rohit is drawn forward in defense but is beaten.
Solid this time! On off, Rohit with his bat close to his pad, keeps it out.
On the pads, this is worked towards fine leg for one.

FOUR! What a shot that is! It is fuller and on middle, comes back in too. Rahul gets his front leg out of the way and creams it through mid off for another boundary. He is another boundary away from a half ton now.
Curran drags his length back and bowls it on middle, blocked.
NO BALL! Curran oversteps again! On middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket for one.
Nothing from the extra ball! Outside off, left alone.

Would have been close! Rohit would have been out! England need to take such chances! Shorter and on middle, this is worked towards the leg side. Rahul calls for one. Rohit is a little late in taking off. The fielder at mid-wicket gets to the ball, picks it up and fires it at the keeper's end as he falls on the ground. He misses.
Outside off, left alone.

OUT! TAKEN! England strike at the stroke of Lunch! Rohit once again falls in the 30s! Ollie Robinson is absolutely delighted. That gut feeling, we did mention, Ollie Robinson might be the man for England today, yes, he has got just the one wicket but it is the wicket England so desperately wanted and this could well be the opening they needed. Rohit Sharma is gutted as he walks back. He probably could have just let it go to the keeper but this shot is so instinctive, it comes to him so naturally that even unwantingly he ends up playing it. A surprise short one by Ollie! It is a good one too, on the body. Rohit looks to pull but fails to control it, it goes off the top edge and to the fine leg fielder where Curran takes it. A superb opening stand comes to an end. INDIA TRAIL BY 86! THAT WILL ALSO BE LUNCH!
Howout: c Sam Curran b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Back of a length ball on middle, Pujara hops and tries to defend but gets hit on the tummy.
Robinson goes full this time, outside off. Pujara leaves it alone.

Pujara is off the mark! Length ball on off, Pujara drives it to cover. The fielder there makes a half stop. The ball rolls further away and the batters take a run. Ollie Robinson has overstepped and the umpire signals a No Ball.
Robinson bangs a bouncer on middle, KL Rahul sits under it.
Good length delivery on off, Pujara stands tall and drives it back to the bowler.
Good length, outside off. Pujara watches the ball closely and lets it go.
On a length on off, Pujara dabs it to the slip cordon.
Length delivery on off, Pujara shoulders arms to that.
Length ball on off, Pujara punches it towards covers for a single.
Good length delivery on middle, coming back in. KL Rahul pushes it back to the bowler.

NOT OUT! Good length delivery on off, coming back in sharply. Cheteshwar Pujara shoulders arms and leaves. He gets hit on the front pad above the knee roll. Ollie Robinson appeals for an LBW and the umpire agrees with him. Cheteshwar Pujara has a conversation with KL Rahul and opts for a review. The Ball Tracker shows wickets missing as it is going over the stumps. A good review taken by India as Pujara survives. India retain their review as well.
Slightly fuller than the last ball, this time Pujara judges the length well again and blocks it.
On off yet again, kept out.
Fuller and on off, Pujara strokes it back to the bowler.
Gets this one to shape away nicely but the line is outside off, left alone. Another no ball as Ollie Robinson has overstepped.
Another one on a length and around off, kept out.
Two! Angled into the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for a couple.
On a length on middle. KL Rahul looks to tuck it on the leg side but gets hit on the thigh pad. The ball rolls on the leg side and the batters take a run.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! James Anderson is always dangerous no matter under what conditions you play in. You cannot keep this man out of this game. Anderson bowls a good length ball on off, nipping away. Cheteshwar Pujara is caught at the crease and has a poke at it. The ball goes off the outside edge and carries through to the keeper. Jos Buttler behind the stumps gulps it down. England are celebrating but the umpires are not sure and they take it upstairs. The soft signal is out. Replay rolls in and Ultra Edge shows there is a spike as the ball passes the bat. Cheteshwar Pujara has to walk back for a timid score. England are all charged up.
Howout: c Jos Buttler b James Anderson

Commentary: OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! The crowd is going bonkers! Anderson is on cloud 9 and so are the English players! They have got Virat Kohli on the first ball. Kohli can't believe it as he holds his ground for a second. What have England had for Lunch! Whatever it maybe, it has surely changed their fortunes. We saw edges fall short and find the gap in the first session. Now, Anderson has managed to find the edge on two consecutive balls and both have carried. All of a sudden, England are back into the game. The first battle of this series between Anderson and Kohli has been won by Anderson. This is on a length and around off, holds its line. Kohli probably could have left it but since he is new to the crease, he wanted to feel bat on ball. He pokes at it, it goes off the outside edge and it is taken by Jos Buttler. India still 79 runs away.
Howout: c Jos Buttler b James Anderson

Commentary: Length delivery down the leg, Rahane leaves it alone. No hat-trick for Anderson but look how the tables have turned.
Good length ball on off, Rahane pushes it to covers.
Anderson sprays this one well down the leg side, Rahane shoulders arms. The crowd is going bonkers at the moment.

Fifty for Rahul! Back into the side and back amongst the runs! Talk about grabbing an opportunity and he has done well so far. Tough conditions and he has really fought it out well. Needs to go on now. This is fuller and outside off, he guides it through point for two.
Back of a length and on middle, blocked.
Back of a length and on middle, Rahul nudges it to mid-wicket.
Fuller and outside off, Rahul shoulders arms to this one.
Angled into the pads, Rahul works it through wide mid on for one.

OVERTHROWS! Rahane is off the mark! A direct hit though and he was a goner too. Back of a length and on off, Rahane looks to drop and run. The fielder at covers runs towards the ball, picks it up and has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. No one backing up and they take three more.
On a length on off, Rahul taps it to point from the crease.
Good length ball down the leg side, Rahul misses his flick. Good take by Jos Buttler behind the stumps as he dives to his left to collect it.
Good length ball on off, swinging in. Rahul defends it out.
Back of a length on off, Rahul pushes it towards point.
An inswinging yorker on off, Rahul clears his front leg and squeezes it out to point.
Fuller and outside off, Rahul lets it sail through.
Length ball on middle, Rahane covers his stumps and tickles it to fine leg for a single.

OUT! RUN OUT! Are we witnessing another Indian collapse? Robinson pitches it on a length on off, KL Rahul hops and defends it towards point. He calls for a single but sees Jonny Bairstow coming in quickly and yells a big 'NO'. Ajinkya Rahane meantime has already been halfway down the pitch. He runs back to make it to the crease but Jonny Bairstow is too quick as he fires a throw at the non-strikers' end and hits the bull's eye. Rahane is well out and has to continue his run back to the pavilion. This is the last thing that India would have wanted.
Howout: run out (Jonny Bairstow)

Commentary: Short and on middle, Rahul sways away from it.
Outside off, Rahul lets it sail through.
Short ball on middle, Rahul again sways away from it.
Full and outside off, Rahul leaves it alone.
Good length ball on the fifth-stump line. Pant leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Length ball outside off, Pant cuts it well but finds backward point.
BEATEN! Fuller length outside off, swinging away. Pant tries to drive it but misses.
Length ball on off, Pant shimmies down and lifts it over covers. The fielder from cover gives it a chase and cuts it off. Three runs taken.
On a length on off, Rahul blocks it out.

EDGED BUT SAFE! Good length ball on off, Rahul has a poke at it. The ball kisses the outside edge and flies to the slip cordon. Dominic Sibley attempts to take the catch with a dive but it falls just short of him. It actually was not short, IT DID CARRY! An opportunity goes abegging and that too a big one as it was of Rahul. Could prove costly.
FOUR! In the gap! Length delivery on off, Rishabh Pant prods and drives it through covers. The fielder gives it a chase but to no success. A boundary.
On a length on middle and leg, Pant looks to whip it away but misses. He gets hit on the thigh pad and the ball rolls on the leg side. The batters sneak a leg bye.
FOUR! Deft touch! Length delivery on off, KL Rahul guides it with soft hands through the slip cordon to the third man region for a boundary.
Short of a length on middle, Rahul tucks it around the corner for a run.
Outside off, left alone by Pant.
Length delivery on off, Pant taps it to point.
An inswinger on off, Rahul defends it off the front foot.
Excellent start after the break! Good length delivery on off, comes back in lately. KL Rahul puts a stride forward and tries to defend. He gets beaten on the outside edge.
Anderson again steams in and bowls a good length on off, KL Rahul pushes it to point.
Length delivery on middle, Rahul nudges it to mid-wicket.
Right on the money. Serves a full length ball, on off. KL Rahul defends it to cover and rotates the strike straight away.
After a day's break, Anderson finally completes his over. A length ball, on the bodyline. Pant tucks it towards mid-wicket.
A bit of an away movement to start with. A length ball, outside off, nipping away. Rahul lets it go to the keeper.
Serves a length ball now, down the leg. Rahul leaves it alone. Jos Buttler collects it behind the stumps to his left.
A bit straighter this time. A good lenght ball, just outside off. The ball hold its line after pitching. Rahul shoulders his arms.
A full length ball, around off, coming back in. Rahul keeps his eyes on the ball and defends it out solidly.

Some hesitation now. Serves a full length ball, on the pads. Rahul tucks it to mid-wicket and calls for a run. But he sees that the fielder is quick enough to collect the ball. The batter was sent back in the end.
Good away movement to end the over. A good lenght ball, outside off, swinging away. Rahul shoulders his arms.
Dishes a good length ball, outside off. Pant lets it go to the keeper.
A full length ball, around middle and leg. Pant tucks it past mid-wicket fielder for a couple.
FOUR! Hammered! Pant has taken the attack back to James Anderson. A length ball, on off. Pant dances down the track and slashes it past mid off. The ball races away to the boundary.

Some appeal strightaway. Back of a length ball, outside off. Rishabh Pant stays back and looks to go after it but misses it completely. The keeper and the slip cordon along with Anderson heard a nick and were jumping in the air, hoping the umpire raises his finger. But the umpire was unmoved. Joe Root has a word with his team-mates and does not go for the review.
A full length ball, on off. Pant defends it out watchfully.
Serves a length ball, on the pads. Pant tucks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Robinson starts with a back of a length ball, on off. Pant stays back and hooks it towards square leg. They take one. And in no time, the drizzle is back on.
LEG BYE! A touch short, on the pads. Rahul looks to flick it away but misses. The ball clips the thigh pads and goes towards fine leg. They collect a leg bye.
Hurls a length ball, on off. Pant defends it to cover. He ventures out looking for a single, but was sent back to his crease.

FOUR! EDGY! A full length ball, on off. Pant looks to defend it out. The ball though takes the outside edge and flies past the man at gully. The man there put in a dive to his left, but nowhere near the ball. The ball races away to the boundary.

SIX! EDGY AGAIN! Back of a length ball, on middle. Pant stays back and looks to pull it away. The ball takes the top edge and flies over the keeper's head. The ball ends up in the boundary at third man for a maximum.

OUT! CAUGHT! Four, six and out. Ollie Robinson has the last laugh here. Not a great start for India on Day 3, as Pant walks out early. Serves a full length ball, on off. Pant defends it out but with soft hands. He chips it towards cover but straight to the man present there. Jonny Bairstow takes the simplest of catches and Pant has to walk back to the shed.
Howout: c Jonny Bairstow b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: A good length ball, outside off. Rahul leaves it alone.
Another good length ball, outside off, swinging away, Rahul has no stroke to offer.
A full length ball, on off. Rahul tucks it to mid-wicket.

Will Joe Root takes it upstairs? No they won't. Serves a length ball, on the fourth stump line, coming back in. Rahul prods and looks to defend it out but misses and gets hit on the pads. Anderson and company make a loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved. England only have a single review left now, so they did not go for it. And smartly enough it worked in their favour, as the replays rolled in and confirmed that the impast was outside the line.
FOUR! What a reply by KL Rahul. Anderson dishes it full and outside off. Rahul stays back and drives it square on the off side. It goes through point for a boundary.
A length ball, on off. Rahul defends it out solidly.

FOUR! Off the gloves! A length ball, around the hips. Jadeja hops and looks to clip it. The ball though hit his gloves and goes towards fine leg. It races away to the boundary. First runs for Ravindra Jadeja.
A length ball, on leg. Jadeja tucks it to square leg.
BEATEN! Beautifully bowled. A length ball, outside off. Coming across the batsman. Jadeja looks to defend it out but misses. The ball beats the outside edge.
A full length ball, on off. Jadeja is solid in his defense.
Serves it full and just outside off. Jadeja stays back and blocks it to cover.
Just a boundary of the over then. Good length ball, outside off. Jadeja lets it go through to the keeper.
Hurls a length ball, on off. Rahul stays back and defends it out watchfully.
Well left! A good length ball, outside off. The ball stays straight after pitching. KL Rahul watchfully shoulders his arms.
A good length ball, around off. Rahul taps it to point.
Good running! A full length ball, on middle and off. Rahul flicks it towards mid on and takes off for a single.
Good length ball, outside off. Jadeja shoulders his arms.
A full length ball, around off, this one came back in. But, Ravindra Jadeja was equal to the task, as he blocks it back to the bowler. India trail by 29 runs.

A direct hit and Jadeja was a goner. A length ball, on off. Rahul pushes it to cover and calls for a run. There is  a bit of a mix-up and Jadeja was late to react to his call. The fielder collects the ball and has a shy at the striker's end. Ravindra Jadeja was not even in the frame when the ball passed the wickets. In the end, the batters get a single.
A length ball, outside off. Rahul lets it go to the keeper.
Serves a good length ball, outside off. Jadeja does not have any stroke to offer.
A full length ball, on the pads. Jadeja clips it through mid-wicket. The batters take an easy couple.
Effort ball this time. Serves it on a length, outside off. The ball gets an extra bounce after hitting the deck. Ravindra Jadeja pulls his bat back.
BEAUTY! A length ball, around off, moving away. Jadeja looks to defend it out but misses. The ball whistles past the outside edge.
Starts with a full length ball, on off. Rahul blocks it out watchfully.
A length ball, around off. Rahul works it towards mid on.
Rahul gets squared up. A length ball, on off. Rahul looks to defend it with a straight bat. The ball though takes the outer half and rolls towards point.
A risky leave! Serves a length ball, on the fourth stump line. Rahul wanted to defend it out but pulled his bat back in time. The ball goes past the off stump.
A good length ball, outside off. KL Rahul lets it go to the keeper.
A maiden for Stuart Broad. Good length ball, outside off. Rahul does not have any stroke to offer.
Good away movement this time. Serves a good length ball, around off, moving away. Jadeja lets it go to the keeper.
BEAUTY! A length ball, around off, the away movement continues for him. Jadeja looks to play inside the line but misses.
Good length ball, outside off. Jadeja looks to defend it out. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Jadeja is beaten again. This is some good spell from Ollie Robinson. Hurls it on a length, around off, nipping away. Jadeja put his bat  out to block it out but misses it completely.
A full length ball, on the pads. Jadeja clips it towards square leg and rotates the strike.

JAFFA! Ollie Robinson gets KL Rahul squared up. A length ball, in the corridor of uncertainty. Rahul moves across and looks to defend it out but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge. Ollie Robinson with a top spell this time.
A full length ball, on middle, Jadeja flicks it through the leg side for a single.
Good length ball, outside off. Rahul leaves it alone.
Back of a length ball, on the bodyline. Rahul moves across and looks to pull it away but misses.
Nice movement on this one. Serves it on a length, outside off. The ball nips back in. Rahul lets it go to the keeper.
A length ball, on off. Rahul defends it to cover and as soon as he does that he yells a NO for a single. Maybe he has learnt his lesson. He is making sure he communicate clearly now.
A full length ball, on off. Rahul pushes it past mid off. The batters take a couple before the fielder cuts it out.
Touch fuller and on the pads. Jadeja looks to defend but gets outer half of his blade towards point.
Full ball, slanting across, outside off. Jadeja lets it through to the keeper.
Length ball way outside off. Jadeja leaves it alone.
Another good length ball, way outside off. Jadeja leaves it to the keeper.
FOUR! Helped away! A length ball, down the leg side. Jadeja clips it fine and well wide of the diving keeper to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Full ball, angling across, outside off. Left alone.
On a length and way outside off. Rahul watchfully leaves it to the keeper.
A length ball on middle. Rahul looks to defend but gets outer half of his bat, towards point.
FOUR! Well played! A good length ball on middle. Rahul punches off the back foot through point for a boundary. Jonny Bairstow from point chases it but to no avail.
A length ball, outside off, shaping away. Rahul shoulders arms to it.
Good leave! A short of a length ball on middle. Rahul sways away from it.

NOT OUT! A good length ball, around off. The ball straightens up off the deck. Rahul hangs his bat out and looks to defend but misses. The keeper collects the ball and appeals for caught behind straightaway. There was some noise as the ball passed the bat, which gave hope to the English players. So, they take the review and the Ultra edge shows no bat on it. England lose all their reviews.
Two taken! A full toss, on the pads. Jadeja clips it to deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Full and angling on the pads. Jadeja looks to flick but misses. England optimistically appeal but it was clearly angling down.
Around off, a fuller ball. Jadeja pushes it to covers.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! Curran looks for the swing but bowls it very full and on middle, it shapes away as well. Rahul pushes it straight down the ground and the ball races away to the fence.
On middle, a fuller length. Jadeja tucks it to mid on.
On a length and on off. Jadeja defends it off the front foot.
Full and on off. Rahul pushes it to sweeper cover for a single.
A full ball on middle. Jadeja defends it to the leg side.
Another full ball on off. Jadeja punches it back to the bowler.
A fullish length ball on the pads. Jadeja comes across the line and clips it to fine leg and runs across for a single.
BEATEN! On a length and outside off. Rahul takes a big stride forward and looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Touch fuller now and outside off, shaping away from the batter. Rahul shoulders arms to it.
An outswinger this time. Full and around off, swinging away. Jadeja is up to the task and defends it out solidly.
A bit full, on the pads. Jadeja flicks it towards deep square leg for a single. Curran is yet to find his line and length here.
Hurls a  full length ball, outside off. Rahul pushes it to point, straight to the fielder.
That's a much better length by Sam Curran. Serves a length ball, around off. Making Rahul play at it. He does so, as he defends it out watchfully.
A good length ball, around middle and off. Rahul blocks it to the leg side.
EDGY! Serves a full length ball, around off. Rahul looks to defend it out, without moving his feet. The ball take the outside edge and meets the slip on a bounce. Rahul survives.
A fuller ball, around off. Jadeja pushes it to covers.
Good leave! A good length ball, angling just around the off stump. Jadeja watchfully leaves it.
Another full ball on off. Jadeja pushes it to covers.
On a length and on off. Jadeja blocks it off the front foot.
A pacy short ball on middle. Jadeja sits under it and lets it through to the keeper.
FOUR! Lovely timing! A full ball, angling on middle. Jadeja drives it wide of mid on and the ball races away to the long on fence. India trails by 1 run now.
On a length and on off. Rahul taps it under his eyes, the second slip catches it on a bounce.
Full ball, swinging in, on the pads. Rahul flicks it to the leg side and scampers across for a single. Scores are level now.
A good length ball way outside off. Left alone.
Another good length ball outside off and shaping away from the batter. Jadeja lets it through to the keeper.
A touch fuller ball, on middle. Jadeja nudges it to mid-wicket.
Ends the over with a short ball, outside off. Jadeja watches it sail to the keeper.
Three runs taken! A length ball, around off. Rahul stays back and punches it through point. The fielder chases it and does well to save a single for his team.
A good length ball, on the pads. Jadeja misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. Slight appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire.
A full ball, slanting across, outside off. Shoulders arms to it.
On a length and on the pads, flicked to deep square leg for a brace.
A good length ball on off. Jadeja defends it to covers.
BEAUTY! A length ball, angling across, just around off. Ravindra Jadeja looks to defend but the ball whizzes past the outside edge and to the keeper.
Comes around the wicket and bowls a length ball on middle. Rahul defends it on the off side.
Another length ball on off. Rahul punches it past point for a single.
Slight fuller and on middle. Jadeja pushes it to mid on and calls for a quick single. Gets it with ease in the end.
Around off, on a length. Rahul blocks it on the off side.
Serves a very full ball, outside off. Rahul knocks it to the third man for a single.
A full ball, outside off, shapes away very late. Jadeja is not tempted and lets it through to the keeper. That will be LUNCH on DAY 3. India are 191 for 5, and lead by 8 runs.
Serves a length ball, on off. Rahul defends it to cover for a single.
LEG BYE! A full length ball, around leg. Ravindra Jadeja stays back and looks to flick it away but misses. The ball clips the pads and goes towards fine leg. They collect a leg bye.
A full length ball, on off. Rahul pushes it towards mid on.
A full length ball, on off. Rahul pushes it towards mid on.
A length ball, on off. Rahul blocks it out solidly.
Around off, Rahul strides forwards and defends it with his inner half.
Serves a back of a length ball, around off. Jadeja goes back and defends it out solidly.

FOUR! Nicely played. A full length ball, on the pads. Jadeja removes his front leg and flicks it through mid-wicket. The fielder gives it a chase, but the ball wins the race to the ropes. He moves to 31.
Back of a length ball, on middle. Jadeja smartly ducks under this one.
Broad hits the deck hard this time. Serves it on a length, around off. Jadeja works it to the leg side for a single.
Back of a length ball, on off. Rahul ducks under this one.

BYE! Back of a length ball, outside off. The ball nips in after pitching. Rahul ducks under it. The ball goes to the left of Jos Buttler, who fails to grab it. The ball goes towards fine leg. The batters sneak a bye. India lead by 16 now.
Anderson fires in a full length ball, on middle. Rahul stays back and clips it through square leg for a couple of runs.
FOUR! That is some placement by KL Rahul. A touch fuller, just outside off. Rahul leans in and creams it through the cover region for a boundary.
OUCH! That must've hurt. A back of a length ball, on the bodyline. The ball does not get enough bounce off the pitch. Rahul though decides to duck under it but get hit on his back.
A full length ball, on off. Rahul defends it out solidly.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! James Anderson finally finds the early breakthorugh in the second session. And it's the main man KL Rahul, he trudges back on 84, he will be disappointed with himself. This wicket should help England a lot with their confidence now. Anderson serves a length ball, outside off. It nips in a bit in the end. Rahul looks to defend it out but misses it completely. The ball though kisses the outside edge and goes towards the keeper. Jos Buttler does not drop this one and finally there is some joy in the English camp.
Howout: c Jos Buttler b James Anderson

Commentary: A length ball, on off. Thakur defends it out solidly.
Back of a length ball, down the leg side. Jadeja leaves it alone. The ball ends up with the keeper.
Continues with the short ball. This time on middle. Jadeja ducks under this one.
A length ball, around off, coming back in. Jadeja defends it with a straight bat.
A length ball, outside off. Jadeja shoulders his arms without any second thoughts.
A length ball, down the leg side. RJ leaves it alone.
A length ball, outside off. Jadeja works it towards cover.
Serves a length ball, around off. Thakur pushes it back to the bowler.
A full length ball, on off. Thakur remains solid in his defense.
Short ball now, on middle. Thakur stays back and looks to pull it away but misses.
A length ball, on off. Thakur defends it out solidly.

OUT! CAUGHT! Joe Root does not drop it this time around. The crowd is bouncing along with James Anderson now. Serves a length ball, just outside off. Thakur looks to defend it out but misses. The ball takes the outside edge and flies to the left of Joe Root, at first slip. He takes a brilliant low catch to his left. India slip further. James Anderson picks up his fourth wicket now. What a game he is having.
Howout: c Joe Root b James Anderson

Commentary: A full length ball, on off. Shami defends it out solidly.
Back of a length ball, on off. Jadeja hooks it towards deep square leg. They pick a couple.
Hurls a length ball, around off. RJ looks to defend it out but misses. The away movement of the ball makes it difficult for Jadeja to tap it out.
A short ball, on the bodyline. Jadeja ducks under this one.
Back of a length ball, on off. Jadeja ducks again.
A length ball, outside off. Jadeja dabs it to gully.
A touch short, around off. Jadeja pulls it towards square leg for a run. He keeps the strike.
A length ball, outside off. Jadeja cuts it towards backward point. Zak Crawley stops it brilliantly.
A back of a length ball, around off. Jadeja hops and defends it towards point.

FOUR! Lucky, just over gully. Anderson serves a length ball, around off. The ball takes off after hitting the deck. Jadeja is surprised by the extra bounce. He looks to defend it out. The ball takes the outside edge and goes over the man at gully for a boundary.
A length ball, outside off. Jadeja cuts it through point.
SIX! Helped away! Anderson fires in a full length ball, on the pads. Jadeja flicks it over the square leg fence for a maximum. Strong hands. The ball is lost in the stands.
Serves a length ball, around off. Jadeja throws the sink at it but misses. The ball goes past the off stump.
A length delivery, outside off. Shami pushes it through covers. The batters collect three, before the fielder cuts it off.
Back of a length ball, on the bodyline. Jadeja looks to pull it away but instead pulls his blade back.
A full length ball, on leg. Jadeja clips it towards fine leg.
A length ball, around off. Jadeja blocks it to the off side.

Direct Hit and Shami was a goner! A length ball, on off. Jadeja taps it to Rory Burns at gully. He takes off for a single. Burns collects the ball and misses his shy at the striker's end. The batters get one.
A length ball, outside off. Shami leaves it alone.

FOUR! Jadeja is straightaway on the attack. A length ball, outside off. Jadeja stays back and cuts it through point for a boundary. This also brings up his half century and out comes the sword celebration by Ravindra Jadeja. What a handy innings.
A length ball, on off. Jadeja stays back and pushes it through cover for a couple.
Back of a length ball, on off. Jadeja works it towards gully.
FOUR! Second boundary of the over. A full length ball, on off. Jadeja rocks back and whips it through mid on for a boundary.
Robinson serves a full length ball, outside off. Jadeja looks to go after it but misses.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ollie Robinson comes into the attack and completes his job by getting the wicket of Ravindra Jadeja. This is also the final nail in the coffin. Jadeja's intent was pretty clear, he was going after every ball after getting his fifty. Robinson serves a full length ball, on off. Jadeja stays back and throws his bat at it. He does not middle it though. In fact, he hits it with the toe end of the bat. The ball flies high in the air and goes towards mid off. Stuart Broad runs backward and take a sharp catch by keeping his eyes on the ball.
Howout: c Stuart Broad b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: A length ball, on off. Shami blocks it out solidly.
On middle, Shami defends it out watchfully.
A touch fuller, on the pads. Shami flicks it uppishly towards deep square leg for a couple now.

DROPPED! A length ball, on off. Shami moves away and gets under it. He lifts it high in the air, towards mid on. James Anderson comes running under it, grabs the ball, but it spills out. Shami gets two runs. England are not having a good day in the field.

In the air, safe! A full length ball, on off. Shami powers it towards long on. James Anderson again looks to go after the aerial ball. The breeze though changes the direction of the ball and it lands safely in front of Anderson. Shami gets two more.
BEATEN! A slower, length ball, around off. Shami looks to defend it out but misses.
A full length ball, on the pads. Bumrah is off the mark on his first delivery, as he tucks it to mid-wicket for a run.

A mix-up, but no harm for the tourists. A length ball, on off. Shami looks to work it on the leg side. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards mid off. Shami wanted a single, but Bumrah was not interested. But when Bumrah thought of crossing, Shami refuses to do the same. The fielder collects the ball and has a shy at the non-striker's end but misses.
Short, on off. Shami looks to pull it away but misses.
A length ball, outside off. Shami guides it towards point. Jonny Bairstow concedes a couple due to misfield.
A short ball, on off. Shami looks to pull it away but misses.
Back-of-a-length ball, on off. Shami stands back and looks to pull it away but misses again.
A full length ball, on off. Bumrah pushes it out.
Back of a length ball, on middle. Bumrah defends it out.
A short ball, on off. Bumrah defends it out solidly.
Full, on off. Bumrah keeps it out.
Outside off, left alone.
A bumper to end the over. Back of a length ball, on off. Bumrah ducks under it.
A length ball, around middle, nipping in. Shami misses his flick and gets hit on the pads.
A length ball, on off. Shami gets it towards mid-wicket off the inside edge. They take one.
On off, Bumrah defends it out solidly.
Full and outside off. Bumrah looks to go after it but misses.
A length ball, down the leg side. Bumrah misses his flick.
Runs continue to come for India. A length ball, around off. Bumrah pushes it through the off side for a couple.
A length ball, around off. Shami works it uppishly through the point region for a single.
A full length ball, on off. Bumrah defends it out solidly.
A full length ball, on middle. Bumrah tucks it to the leg side.
A good length ball, on off. Bumrah defends it onto the pitch.
Curran serves a full length delivery, outside off. Moving across the batsman. Bumrah looks to defend it out but misses.
Good leave. A length ball, outside off. Bumrah looks to defend but pulls his bat back.
A length ball, outside off. Shami looks to push it away but misses.
A touch short, on the pads. Shami looks to flick it away but misses and get hit on the pads.

OUT! TIMBER! The new ball does the trick for Ollie Robinson. Robinson serves a full length ball, on middle. Shami looks to defend it out but misses. The ball hits him in the pads and goes onto rattle the stumps. Shami was looking really good in the middle, he did enough to survive for so long and add some crucial runs to swell the lead. India lead by 62 runs.
Howout: b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: A length ball, on the pads. Siraj looks to flick it but misses. The ball clips the pads and goes towards the keeper.
A length ball, around off pushed to covers.
FOUR! Welcome boundary! A full length ball, on off. Robinson bowls it in the slot. Siraj stands tall and drills it through mid off for a boundary.
FOUR! Now Bumrah is taking the charge now. A full length ball, on the pads. Bumrah tucks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.

SIX! It's gone all the way. Curran serves a short ball, on off. Bumrah rocks back and pulls it over the square leg fence for a maximum. This is most likely the highest number of runs for Bumrah in Test cricket.

FOUR! EDGY! A full length ball, on off. Bumrah looks to defend it out. The ball takes the outside edge and flies over the slip cordon. It ends up in the boundary at third man. So, 14 runs coming off the first three deliveries.
A length ball, outside off, Bumrah looks to go after it but misses.
A length ball, around off. Bumrah stays back and looks to heave it away but misses it completely.

LEG BYE! A fuller length ball, around leg. Bumrah looks to flick it away but misses. The ball clips the pads and rolls to the off side. The batters take a risky single and the umpire signals a leg bye.
A full length ball, on middle. Bumrah drives it through mid on for a couple.
A slower length ball, on off. Bumrah plays it across the line and works it towards mid-wicket.
Back of a length ball, on off. Bumrah looks to pull it away but misses.
A back of a length ball, around off. Bumrah sways away from the line of the delivery.
A short ball again, outside off. Bumrah looks to go after it but misses.

FOUR! England continue to leak runs here. A short ball, on middle. Bumrah looks pull it away. The ball hits the top edge and flies over the keeper's head for a boundary. Jasprit Bumrah is enjoying his batting here.
Anderson serves a  length ball, around off. Siraj moves back and looks to work it on the off side but misses.
A good length delivery, on off. Siraj lifts it over the cover region. The balls lands in a vacant region. The batters take a couple.
Outside off, Siraj looks to heave it away but misses.
A length ball, around off. Siraj looks to work it across the line, but the ball takes the outside edge and meets the fielder at third man on a bounce. They take one.
A full length ball, on middle. Bumrah flicks it through mid-wicket for another single.
Anderson serves a length ball, outside off. Siraj looks to push it away but misses.
Starts this over with a slower one. Robinson serves it full and outside off. Bumrah looks to chase it but misses.
Hurls a length ball, around off, nipping in. Bumrah looks to whack it across the line but misses.
A length ball, on off. Bumrah throws his bat at it. He lofts it over the cover region for a couple.
Two more. A full length ball, on middle. Bumrah flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple. They lead by 95 runs now. Can they make it 100?

OUT! CAUGHT! No the tail-enders could not swell the lead to 100. And finally England are successful to end things here and Ollie Robinson gets his fi-fer. A full length ball, on off. Bumrah looks to go big yet again. But this time he does not connect well. The ball takes the top edge and goes towards fine leg. Stuart Broad covers a lot of ground to his right. He take a good running catch. India end their innings on 287 and they lead by 95 runs.
Howout: c Stuart Broad b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Bumrah starts with a length delivery, on the pads. Burns nudges it to the leg side.
NO BALL! A full length ball, on off. Burns defends it out solidly. The umpire signals a no ball due to overstepping.
A length ball, outside off. Burns looks to defend it out but misses it completely.
Burns is off the mark this time. A length ball, on the pads. Burns glances it to fine leg for a single.
Good length ball, on off. Sibley defends it out.
A length ball, around off. Sibley stays back and pushes it back to the bowler.
A length ball, outside off. Sibley leaves it alone.
Siraj begins with a lenght ball, outside off, moving away. Burns leaves it alone for the keeper.
A good length ball, outside off, moving away. Burns leaves it alone.
Burns leaves it for the third time now. Serves it on a length, outside off, slanting away. Burns lets it go to the keeper.
Siraj serves it on a length, around off. The ball moves away off the pitch. Burns is happy to leave it.
Finally Burns gets a bat to this one. Siraj serves a length ball, around off. Burns was late into his shot. But he defends it out with an angled bat.
A good length ball, around off. Burns stays back and blocks it to the off side.
A length ball, way outside off. The ball takes off after hitting the deck. Sibley watches it sail past him to the keeper.
Bumrah fires in a full length ball, on off. Sibley defends it with a straight bat.
A length ball, on off. Sibley defends it towards mid-wicket.
Bumrah fires in a full length delivery, on off.Sibley defends it towards cover off the front foot.
A full length ball, on off. Sibley blocks it to the leg side.
NO BALL! A length ball, outside off. Sibley leaves it alone. The umpire signals a no ball due to overstepping.
BEATEN! Bumrah dishes a length ball, on the fourth stump line. Sibley stays back and looks to defend it out but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
A full length ball, on off. Burns defends it out solidly.
A length delivery, on middle and off. Burns stays back and defends it out.
A length ball, on middle. Burns tucks it towards square leg.
A full length delivery, on off. Burns pushes it to mid off.
Five dots on the trot! Siraj serves a full length ball, outside off. Burns shoulders his arms. Can Mohammed Siraj make it two maidens in a row?
Yes he does. Second maiden for Siraj. A length ball, on off. Burns defends it onto the pitch. The ball though bounces over the stumps. Siraj has his hands behind his head.
A full length ball, on off. Sibley defends it back to the bowler.
NO BALL! A good length ball, outside off. Sibley shoulders his arms. Umpire signals a no ball for overstepping. This is the third time Bumrah oversteps.
A length ball, on off. Sibley defends it out.
WIDE! Back of a length ball, on off. Sibley ducks under it. The umpire signals a wide because of the height.
Good movement on this one. Good length ball, outside off, coming back in. Sibley shoulders his arms.
Bumrah fires in a length ball, around off. Sibley blocks it onto his pads.
Hurls in a full length delivery, on off. Sibley blocks it with a straight bat.
Finallt, Sibley gets off the mark! A length ball, on the pads. Sibley flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
FOUR! Nicely played. A full length ball, on the pads. Sibley stays back and works it through sqaure leg for a boundary. As the ball got near to he ropes, the crowd got louder.
Outside off, left alone.

OUCH! A length ball, on middle and leg. Sibley looks to defend it out but misses and gets hit high on the pad. Siraj makes an appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Sibley looks in some pain here. But he does not want the physio to walk out.
A full length ball, on off, Sibley keeps it out.
Back of a length ball, on off. Sibley ducks under this one. Umpire signals a no ball, as this time it is Siraj who oversteps.
Another short ball, on middle. Sibley ducks under it.
Good length ball, on off, Sibley clips it to the leg side. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 3.

Shami starts really well, he gets the outside edge into play in the first delivery. A length ball, on off. Burns stays back and looks to defend it out. The ball takes the outside edge but it does not carry towards gully.
BEATEN! Mohammed Shami continues to impress. He serves a length ball, on the fourth stump line. Burns looks to defend it out but misses. The ball beats the outside edge.
Good length ball, on off. Burns works it to the leg side.
A length ball, on middle. Burns clips it towards square leg.
Shami serves a length ball, on off. Burns defends it back to the bowler.
On a length, outside off. Burns defends it out watchfully.
FOUR! EDGY! Siraj fires in a full length ball, on off. Sibley looks to defend it out. The ball takes the outside edge and rolls towards third man for a boundary.
A good length ball, outside off, moving away. Sibley shoulders his arms to it.
A length ball, outside off. Sibley leaves it alone.
A full length ball, on middle. Sibley tucks it to short mid-wicket, where KL Rahul makes a brilliant stop.
Effort ball this time. Siraj serves it on a length, outside off. SIbley shoulders his arms.
CLOSE! A length ball, outside off. Sibley looks to defend it out but misses. The ball beats the outside edge, but it dies on its way to the keeper. Just a boundary off the over then.
Shami continues to come around the wicket. He serves a length ball, around off. Burns defends it to the off side.
Some inward movement this time. Good length ball, outside off, nipping in. Burns shoulders his arms.
A touch fuller this time, around off. Burns goes on one knee and drives it towards point.
FOUR! Clipped away! Burns is really good off his pads. A touch too straight from Shami. He serves it full and on the pads. Shami clips it through mi-wicket for a boundary.
Shami goes again for the pads. A full length ball, on leg. Burns tucks it through mid-wicket for a single.
A length ball, on off. Sibley defends it out watchfully.
Good length ball, outside off. Burns leaves it alone.
Serves a full length ball, on off. Burns defends it towards mid-wicket.
Siraj dishes a length ball, on off. Burns goes back and defends it with a straight bat.
A full length ball on off. Burns defends it back to the bowler.
A length ball, down the leg side. Burns clips it through square leg for a single.
Siraj serves it on a length, outside off. Sibley shoulders his arms. A nice over by Mohammed Siraj.
A length ball, on off. Burns pushes it toward mid on.
BEATEN! A full length ball, outside off. Burns looks to defend it out but misses. The ball beats the outside edge.
A length ball, on off. Burns stays back and defends it out watcfully.
On off, defended solidly.
FOUR! EDGY! A full length ball, outside off. Burns hangs his bat out as he looks to defend it. The ball takes the outside edge and rolls past gully. The ball ends up in the boundary at third man.
A good length ball, outside off, nipping in. Burns shoulders his arms.
A full length ball, on off. Sibley prods and defends it out watchfully.
Siraj starts with an inswinger. Full and on the pads. Sibley stays back and flicks it towards fine leg for a couple. Runs straightaway for England.
A full length ball, on off, Sibley prods and defends it out solidly.
Keeps it full yet again, on off. Sibley takes a step forward and blocks it out.
A bumper now. Back of a length ball, on off. The ball gets an extra bounce off the pitch. Dominic Sibley ducks under it.

A loud appeal for LBW but turned down. What a way to end the over. Some inward movement this time. Siraj serves a length ball, around off, nipping in. Sibley looks to defend but misses and gets rapped on the pads. Siraj appeals but the umpire is unmoved. Virat Kohli is asking his players only one question, if it was way too high? And in the end, they don't opt for the review.
Bumrah starts from around the wicket. A length ball, outside off. Burns leaves it alone.
Bumrah fires in a full length delivery, on the pads. Burns clips it towards deep mid-wicket. Mohammed Siraj fumbles in the deep and the batters take an easy two.
NO BALL! A good length ball, outside off. Burns shoulders his arms. Jasprit Bumrah oversteps and the umpire signals a no ball.
A full length ball, on off. Burns defends it out solidly.
Some away movement this time. Bumrah serves it on a length, outside off, moving away. Burns is happy to leave that one.
FOUR! Clipped away nicely. A length ball, on the pads. Burns stays back and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On a length, on the fourth stump line. Burns moves across and defends it onto the pitch.
A length ball, on off. Sibley works it through mid-wicket off the inner half. They take one.
Siraj serves a good length ball,, going across the left-hander. Burns lets it go to the keeper.
A length ball, on the pads. The ball stays straight after pitching. Burns clips it through square leg for a single.
A full length ball, on off. Sibley defends it out solidly.
A good length ball, around off. Sibley looks to defend it with a straight bat. The ball goes towards cover off the outer half. The batters take a quick single.
On a length, outside off., moving away. Burns shoulders his arms. Just 3 runs off the over.

Bumrah serves a length ball, around off. Sibley stays back and defends it towards gully. The batters were looking for a run, but then they realised Ravindra Jadeja had collected the ball and smartly opted out of the run.
A full length ball, on off. Sibley defends it out watchfully.
CLOSE! Back of a length ball, on the fourth stump line. The ball hold its line after pitching. Sibley looks to defend it out, but the ball beats the outside edge.
A length ball, on off. Sibley blocks it out watchfully.

Brilliant from Ajinkya Rahane. A direct hit and Dominic Sibley was a goner. Bumrah serves a length ball, around off. Sibley defends it to the right of gully. Ajinkya Rahane dives to his right to make a sharp stop. Meanwhile, Sibley ventures out looking for a run. He was sent back by Burns, but was not early to react on that. Rahane has a shy on the keeper's end but misses.
A length ball, outside off. Sibley shoulders his arms.

OUT! CAUGHT! Mohammed Siraj gets the first wicket of the day and draws the first blood. This is why he was given the ball and it paid off really well for India. The early breakthrough will put some pressure on England now. Siraj serves a good length ball, around off. Moving away from the batsman. Burns looks to defend it out. The ball though kisses the outside edge and goes towards the keeper. Rishabh Pant moves a bit to his left and takes an easy catch. Brilliant start for India.
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: FOUR! STREAKY! Good length ball, on off. Zak Crawley defends it with hard hands and the ball goes towards the boundary as it beats the gully fielder.
Length ball, outside off. Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
An inswinger from Siraj this time. Zak Crawley comes forward and flicks it wide of mid on for a couple of runs.
Serves a length ball, outside off. Zak Crawley shoulders arms to it.
Full length ball, outside off. Zak Crawley comes forward and lets it go through to the keeper.
A length ball, on off, Sibley stays back and defends it to the leg side.
Keeps it full this time. On middle and off. Sibley clips it towards square leg. The batters take a couple.
Bumrah serves it on a length, just outside off. Sibley defends it with a straight bat.
A length ball, on the pads. Sibley tucks it to the right of square leg and takes off for a single.
Bumrah fires in a full length delivery, around off. Crawley defends it out with an angled bat.

OUT! CAUGHT! Zak Crawley departs after another poor performance in this Test match. The pacers are making the ball dance to their tunes. It's all India at the moment. Bumrah dishes a full length ball, around off. The ball nips away a bit after pitching. Crawley tried to defend it out, but only managed to get a thick outside edge. The ball goes towards the keeper. Rishabh Pant dives to his right and takes an incredible low catch. England lose their second wicket in no time and Jasprit Bumrah continues to shine in the game.
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary: A length ball, on off. Sibley defends it out watchfully.
On a length, around off. Making the batsman play at it. Sibley is up to the task and blocks it out solidly.
First time we are seeing some away movement from Mohammed Siraj. A good length ball, outside off, moving away. Dominic Sibley shoulders his arms.
A full length ball, on off. Sibley tucks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Good length ball, outside off. Root moves across and lets it go to the keeper.
Siraj ends his over with a good length ball, outside off. It was nowhere near Root. He left that one with ease.
Bumrah fires in a yorker, on the money. Sibley digs it out solidly.
A length ball, on off. Sibley defends it with a straight bat.
A good length ball, around off. Sibley stays back and defends it towards point.
A full toss this time, on off. Sibley keeps it out.
A full length ball, on off. Sibley defends it off his front foot.
A maiden for Jasprit Bumrah now. A good length ball, outside off. Sibley prods and shoulders his arms. A good leave.
FOUR! Cover drive at its best. Root gets off the mark with a boundary. A full length ball, outside off. Root takes a step forward and creams it through covers for a boundary.
A length ball, around off, coming back in. Root defends it out with hard hands.
On a length, outside off. Root drives it to cover.

A full length ball, on off. Root looks to defend it out and does so but with the toe end of the bat. The ball goes onto bounce off the pitch and before it goes anywhere near the stumps. Root made sure to stop the movement off the ball.
EDGY! A full length ball, on off. Root defends it off the inside edge. This is brilliant bowling by Mohammed Siraj.

EDGY, yet again! A full length ball, around off. Root looks to defend it to the off side. But the ball takes the inside egde, scoots past the stumps and goes towards square leg. Root rotates the strike quickly.
Good length ball, angling in. Joe Root blocks it watchfully.
Length ball, outisde off. Joe Root looks to poke at it but leaves it late as the ball nipped after pitching.
FOUR! STREAKY! Length ball, outisde off. Joe Root comes forward to defend but gets an outside edge and the ball goes past the slip fielder for a boundary.
Length ball, angling in sharply. Joe Root rocks back to defend and gets an inside edge almost onto the stumps.
EDGED BUT SAFE! Length ball, angling in just that little bit. Joe Root pokes at it and the ball just falls short of Virat Kohli at first slip.
Good length ball, outside off. Joe Root leaves it alone.
Banged in short. Dominic Sibley ducks under it and lets it go through to the keeper.
Good length ball, down leg. Dominic Sibley tickles it towards fine leg for a single.
FOUR! CRACKING SHOT! Full ball, outside off. Joe Root prods forward and drives it through covers for a boundary. England trails by 34 runs now.
Serves a length ball, around off. Joe Root blocks it towards cover.
Good length ball, on off. Joe Root stays back and defends it watchfully.
FOUR! EASILY DONE! Good length ball, around leg. Joe Root flicks it past mid-wicket for a boundary.
Starts with a length ball, on off. Dominic Sibley defends it on the on side.
Good length ball, comes in sharply. Dominic Sibley gets on the front foot to defend but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
BEATEN! Length ball, on off. Dominic Sibley looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge as the ball nips away slightly after pitching.
Good length ball, outside off. Dominic Sibley leaves it alone.
Length ball, on middle. Dominic Sibley tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Wide of the crease from Shami. Full ball, on middle. Joe Root defends it off the front foot.
Good length ball, on middle. Dominic Sibley flicks it awkwardly towards square leg for one.
Length ball, on off. Joe Root defends it towards point.
Good length ball, around off. Joe Root pushes it off the back foot towards cover.
Good length ball, around leg. Joe Root flicks it towards fine leg for one.
Serves a length ball, outside off. Dominic Sibley leaves it alone and watches it go through to the keeper.
Good length ball, around off. Dominic Sibley blocks it solidly off the back foot.
Length ball, around off. Joe Root taps it towards backward point for one. Ajinkya Rahane dives to stop the ball but fails to do so.
Good length ball, darted on the pads. Dominic Sibley flicks it towards fine leg for a run.
Length ball, outside off. Joe Root inside edges the cover drive towards mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball, angling in. Dominic Sibley defends it towards mid on.
Full ball, angling in. Dominic Sibley on drives it but straight to the mid on fielder.
An inswinger to end the over from Shami. Full and on middle. Dominic Sibley pushes it off the front foot towards mid on.
Good length ball, outside off. Joe Root looks to poke at it but leaves it alone in the end as there is some extra bounce for Shardul Thakur.
Good length ball, on off. Joe Root defends it watchfully.
Full ball, strayed on the pads. Joe Root whips it off his pads towards fine leg for one.
Length ball, angling in. Dominic Sibley works it towards mid-wicket.
Length ball, outside off. Dominic Sibley looks to poke but leaves it in the end as the ball nips away slightly late.
Serves a full ball, outside off. Dominic Sibley shoulders arms to this one.
Wide of the crease from Mohammed Shami. Good length ball, on middle. Joe Root blocks it.
Good length ball, coming in sharply. Joe Root comes forward and defends it solidly towards cover.
FOUR! CLASSY! Full ball, outside off. Joe Root comes forward and drives it through covers for a boundary. Mohammed Siraj gives it a chase but the ball wins.
FOUR! Another full ball, outside off. Joe Root drives it handsomely through covers for another boundary.
Good length ball, around off. Joe Root blocks it off the front foot.
Serves a length ball, outside off. Joe Root shoulders arms to this one.
A full length ball, on off. Sibley drives it but straight to the man at mid off.
CLOSE! Thakur serves it on a length, outside off. The ball nips in off the pitch. Sibley shoulders his arms.
A length ball, on the pads. Sibley tucks it to mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
A good length ball, outside off. Root moves across and shoulders his arms.
Back-of-a-length ball, on off. Root stays back and pulls it through mid-wicket for a single now.
BEAUTY! Nice way to end the over. Dominic Sibley was all squared up. Thakur serves a length ball, around off. Sibley looks to defend it out but misses and gets rapped on the back foot.
A length delivery, around off. Root stays back and defends it watchfully.
On a length, around off. Root rocks back and blocks it to cover.
Shami serves a length ball, on the pads. Root flicks it through square leg. The batters take a couple before the fielder cuts it off.
A length delivery, on off. Root goes back to being defensive and blocks it out.
On a length, just outside the off pole. Root waits and late cuts it to gully. He does not get the connection he was looking for.
Good running! A length ball, on off. Root defends it to point and takes off for a quick single.

LEG BYE! Thakur serves a length ball, on the pads. Root stays back and looks to flick it away but misses. The ball clips the thigh pad and rolls to the leg side. Thakur makes an half appeal, but  the umpire is not interested. The batters collect a leg bye.
A full length ball, on off. Sibley drives it to cover.

OH! Big mix-up. A full length ball, on off. Sibley tucks it to the right of mid on. Sibley wanted the single and ventures out of the crease. In face he was half way down the pitch. Mohammed Siraj collects the ball and throws it at the non-striker's end, which was the wrong end. If he had thrown it at the striker's end. Dominic Sibley was a goner.
A full length ball, on off. Sibley works it past mid on and this time he communicated clearly. So, the batters ended up taking an easy single.
A length ball, around off. Root guides it towards third man for a single.
Good length ball, outside off. Left alone by Sibley.
NO BALL! He oversteps on his first delivery. Flighted full and around off. Root pushes it to cover and take a single. The umpire signals a no ball because of overstepping.
Tossed up, full and on middle. Sibley defends it to the right of the bowler.
Looped up, full and on off. Sibley blocks it out.
On off, blocked out by Dominic Sibley.
Floated and on off, Sibley remains solid in his defense.
Flatter and on off. Dominic Sibley goes back and pushes it to cover.
A single now, as this is eased towards long off.
A full length ball, on off. Sibley defends it out watchfully.
A good length ball, outside off, moving away. Sibley shoulders his arms.
Back of a length ball, outside off. Sibley leaves it alone.

NOT OUT! Dominic Sibley survives. Thakur fires in a length ball, around middle and leg. The ball nips in a bit. Sibley looks to flick it away but misses and gets rapped on the pads. Thakur and company make an appeal. The umpire is satisfied and he raises his index finger. Dominic Sibley has a word with Joe Root and goes for the review straightaway. The Ball Tracker clearly shows that the ball was missing the wicket.
Length ball, on off. Dominic Sibley looks to defend it but gets an outside edge which falls just short of Rohit Sharma at second slip.
Length ball, outside off. Dominic Sibley leaves it alone.
FOUR BYES! Tossed up, just outside off. Joe Root looks to dig it out but misses and the keeper fails to collect it. The ball races away to the boundary.
Flatter ball, outside off. Joe Root leaves it alone.
Quicker ball, on off. Joe Root taps it towards point.
Tossed up, on off. Joe Root sweeps it but straight to the short mid-wicket fielder.
Flatter ball, outside off. Joe Root shoulders arms to this one.

NOT OUT! Joe Root survives and India lose a review. Quicker ball, outside off. Joe Root misjudges the length as he looks to cut the ball and misses it. He gets rapped on the pads. India appeal but umpire turns it down. India opt to review it. the replays show that the impact was outside off. Joe Root survives.
Length ball, on middle. Dominic Sibley flicks it wide of long on for one.
Good length ball, on off. Joe Root taps it towards backward point.
Banged in short. Joe Root looks to guide it over the keeper but misses.
Banged in again, around leg. Joe Root shuffles across to hook it but misses. There is half an appeal from from the keeper but the umpire turns it down.
Good length ball, on off. Joe Root taps it wide of the backward point fielder for a single. England lead by 2 runs now.
Length ball, outside off. Dominic Sibley leaves it alone.
FOUR! NICELY DONE! Flatter ball, around off. Joe Root just guides it late towards third man for a boundary.
Flatter ball, on off. Joe Root looks to cut late but gets an under-edge as he is late on it. They take one.
Tossed up, on off. Dominic Sibley defends it.
Flatter ball, on off. Dominic Sibley rocks back and pushes it to cover.
Flighted ball, on off. Dominic Sibley comes forward and blocks it.
Tossed up, on off. Dominic Sibley looks to defends but gets an outside edge.
Length ball, on middle. Joe Root pushes it to mid on.
Full ball, on off. Joe Root on drives it towards left of the mid on fielder for a couple of runs.
Length ball, around off. Joe Root looks to push it to cover but gets an inside edge towards the keeper.
Banged in short, down leg. Joe Root shuffles across to pull but misses.
Length ball, on off. Joe Root defends it towards point and scampers through for a run.
BEATEN! Good length ball, around off stump. Dominic Sibley comes forward to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Flatter ball, on off. Joe Root defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up, on off. Joe Root sweeps it towards mid-wicket. Jasprit Bumrah fumbles and they take three runs.
Quicker ball, on middle. Turned towards the on side for one.
Flatter ball, around off. Joe Root defends it off the back foot.
Flighted ball, on middle. Joe Root prods forward and blocks it.
Overpitched ball, around off. Joe Root drags it towards point.
Good length ball, around leg. Dominic Sibley tucks it behind square on the leg side for a run.
Good length ball, around middle. Joe Root blocks it solidly off the front foot.
FOUR! Short and a bit wide. Joe Root cuts it hard over the slip cordon for a boundary. And it brings up his FIFTY. What an innings this has been from the England captain.
Length ball, on off. Joe Root defends it towards cover.
Good length ball, outside off. Joe Root looks to poke at it but leaves it in the end.
FOUR! CLASSY! Full ball, strayed on the pads. Joe Root whips it off his pads and wide of the mid on fielder for a boundary.
Tossed up, on off. Dominic Sibley defends it nicely off the front foot.
Quicker ball, on off. Dominic Sibley pushes it towards point.
Flighted ball, outside off. Dominic Sibley defends it towards cover.
Flatter ball, on middle. Dominic Sibley rocks back and works it towards short fine leg.
Tossed up, outside off. Dominic Sibley leaves it alone.
Flighted ball, on off. Dominic Sibley defends it solidly.
On a length, outside off. Joe Root pushes it to cover.
Full ball, angling in sharply. Joe Root comes forward and defends it solidly.
Good length ball, outside off. Joe Root guides it towards third man for a run.
Length ball, outside off. Dominic Sibley shoulders arms to it and lets it go through to the keeper.
Length ball, around off. Dominic Sibley defends it towards cover.
Length ball, around off. Dominic Sibley defends it off the front foot solidly. And the players will take Lunch on Day 4.
Starts with a flatter ball, on off. Joe Root blocks it off the back foot. They take one.
Flighted ball, on off. Dominic Sibley blocks it watchfully.
Quicker ball, around off. Dominic Sibley prods forward to defend.
Flatter ball, on off. Dominic Sibley defends it solidly.
Quicker ball, outside off. Dominic Sibley leaves it alone.
Flighted ball, on middle. Dominic Sibley works it on the leg side.
FOUR! Sprayed down the leg side. Joe Root just tickles it towards fine leg for a boundary.
Serves a good length ball, on off. Joe Root taps it on the off side and takes a quick run.
Good length ball, on off. Dominic Sibley blocks it solidly off the back foot.
WELL BOWLED! Good length ball, outside off. Dominic Sibley leaves it alone as the ball nips away slightly after pitching.
Good length ball, around middle. Dominic Sibley turns it towards the leg side for a run.
Banged in short, outside off. Joe Root pulls it towards square leg for a single.
FOUR! CREAMED IT! Full ball, outside off. Joe Root drives it through covers for a boundary. Lovely timing on that shot!
Serves a length ball, outside off. Joe Root looks to drive but inside edges it towards mid-wicket.
Good length ball, outside off. Joe Root rocks back and cuts it towards deep backward point for an easy single.
Good length ball, angling in, on off. Dominic Sibley defends it solidly.
Full ball, outside off. Dominic Sibley pushes it off the front foot back to the bowler.
Length ball, on off. Dominic Sibley stands tall and defends it towards cover.
Good length ball, on off. Joe Root defends it off the back foot towards the leg side.
Length ball, outside off. Joe Root comes forward and taps it towards gully.
Back-of-a-length ball, on off. Joe Root rocks back and pushes it towards cover.
Good length ball, around off. Joe Root defends it off the back foot towards cover.
Back-of-a-length ball, on off. Joe Root taps it towards second slip to Rohit Sharma. He has a shy at the stumps. The ball hits the stumps and it deflects towards the leg side. They take one.
Length ball, outside off. Joe Root leaves it alone.
Good length ball, outside off. Joe Root hangs back and defends it off the back foot.
Length ball, outside off. Joe Root shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball, around leg. Joe Root turns it towards the leg side for a run.
Length ball, way outside off. Dominic Sibley leaves it alone.
Length ball, outside off, angling in sharply. Dominic Sibley lets it through to the keeper.
Good length ball, on off. Dominic Sibley defends it solidly off the back foot.
Good length ball, around off. Joe Root taps it behind square on the off side.
Good length ball, on middle. Joe Root rocks back to defend it.
Length ball, darted on the pads. Joe Root whips it towards square leg for a run.
Good length ball, outside off. Dominic Sibley leaves it alone as the ball comes back from outside off stump.

OUT! CAUGHT! Dominic Sibley lost his patience there and Jasprit Bumrah, pounced on it and got the breakthrough that India needed. Bumrah serves a full ball, outside off. Dominic Sibley looks to drive on the up, away form his body and gets an inside edge through to the keeper. Rishabh Pant takes a good low diving catch to his left. Huge blow for England as Sibley was looking set in the middle. India will look to make early inroads in this game now.
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary: Length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow leaves it alone.
Full ball, outside off, came back in sharply. Joe Root leaves it late and the ball just goes past his off stump through to the keeper.
Full ball, on off. Joe Root prods forward and defends it solidly.

Good length ball, came back in sharply. Joe Root misses the flick and gets rapped on the pads. India appeal but the umpire turns it down. They were thinking to take a review but they don't go for it in the end. And it turns out to be a smart decision, as the replays rolled in and confirmed that the ball was missing the wickets.
Good length ball, on off. Joe Root defends it solidly.
Length ball, around off. Joe Root pushes it towards cover off the front foot.
FOUR! WOW! A Joe Root SPECIAL! It was a full ball, outside off. Joe Root creams it through covers for a boundary. Mohammed Siraj throws his hands on the deck in frustration.
Good length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow leaves it alone.
Length ball, angling in, outside off. Jonny Bairstow prods forward and shoulders arms to it.
Full ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow lets it go through to the keeper.
Length ball, strayed on the pads. Jonny Bairstow flicks it through mid-wicket and gets off the mark. They take three runs. England lead by 47 runs.
BEATEN! Full ball, outside off. Joe Root looks to drive it through covers but misses and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Good length ball, on off. Joe Root looks to block it but gets an outside edge and the ball falls just short of Virat Kohli at first slip.
Good length ball, around off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it solidly off the back foot.
Length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow taps it towards backward point.
Length ball, around off. Jonny Bairstow pushes it towards cover on the up.

NOT OUT! Good length ball, around middle and leg. Jonny Bairstow looks to flick by jumping in the crease but he misses and gets rapped high on the pads. India take a review as the on-field umpire had turned it down. The replays clearly show that the ball was going over the stumps and it also missed the leg stump. So the on-field decision stays.
A length ball, on off. Jonny Bairstow defends it with a straight bat.
FOUR! Nicely played. A touch short, outside off. Bairstow stays back and punches it through the gap at covers. The ball races away to the boundary.
Length ball, on off. Joe Root taps it towards backward point for one.
Good length ball, angling in sharply. Jonny Bairstow defends it solidly.
Good length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow looks to defend it off the back foot but gets hit high on the bat.
Length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow pushes it to cover on the up.
Back-of-a-length ball, around leg. Jonny Bairstow turns it behind square on the leg side for one. The lead now moves to 53.
Good length ball, outside off, angling in late. Joe Root leaves it alone.
FOUR! Runs straightaway. Shami starts with a loosener this time. A full length ball, outside off. Looked like Bairstow was ready for it. He prods and drives it through point for a boundary.
BEATEN! A nice come back by Shami. He serves a length ball, just outside the off pole. Jonny Bairstow stays back and looks to defend it out but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
A length ball, on off. Bairstow defends it out.
A full length ball, on the pads. Bairstow clips it towards mid-wicket.
A full length delivery on off. Bairstow pushes it towards mid on.
A length ball, around off. Jonny Bairstow taps it to point for a single.
FOUR! Another boundary of the first delivery here for Jonny Bairstow. A length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow stays back and punches it through point for a boundary. Beautiful shot.
A touch short, on off. Bairstow pulls it towards mid-wicket.
Bangs in a short ball, around off. Jonny Bairstow sways away from the line of the delivery.
A full length ball, on the pads. Jonny Bairstow flicks it to deep square leg for a single now.
Another full length ball, on middle. Root clips it towards mid-wicket.
A good length delivery, on off. Root defends it to cover comfortably.
Shami dishes it full and outside off. Bairstow defends it towards the slip cordon. Rohit Sharma, at second slip dives to his right and makes a brilliant stop.

Shami serves a length ball, outside off, coming back in. Jonny Bairstow looks to defend it out but misses and gets rapped on the back leg. Shami makes an appeal for LBW but the umpire is unmoved. Maybe the height was an issue there.
A good length ball, outside off. Bairstow lets it go to the keeper.
A full length ball, on the pads. Bairstow clips it through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
A length ball, on off. Jonny Bairstow defends it out solidly.
A touch fuller and on off. Bairstow blocks it back to the bowler with a straight bat.
Siraj serves a length ball, around off. Root stays back and blocks it to the off side. They take one.
FOUR! Good timing! A touch short, outside off. Bairstow stays back and gets on the top of the ball. He punches it through point for a boundary. This is a confident looking Jonny Bairstow.
A good length ball, on off. Bairstow pushes it to cover.
A full length ball, straying on the pads. Jonny Bairstow clips it to mid-wicket.
Siraj fires in a full length ball, around off. Bairstow works it to cover off the outer half of his blade.
Full length ball, on the pads. Bairstow tucks it to deep square leg for a single. Another good over for England. They lead by 71 runs.
Tossed up and on off. Bairstow defends it to the leg side.
Full and outside off. Bairstow defends it out solidly.
Flatter and short, on off. Bairstow goes back and pushes it to cover.
Darted on the pads. Bairstow clips it through mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Root continues on his merry way. Loopy ball, around middle and leg. Root prods and sweeps it towards fine leg for a boundary.
On off, kept out.
A length ball, on off. Bairstow defends it back to the bowler.
A full length ball, on off. Bairstow defends it to cover.
A length ball, around off. Bairstow looks to defend it, but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
What a beauty by Mohammed Siraj. A length ball, outside off, this one jags in a long way. Jonny Bairstow shoulders his arms. Rishabh Pant does really well by diving to his left to collect the ball.
A touch short, on off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it out.
Full and on off. Bairstow clips it to mid-wicket for a couple.
On off, blocked out.
Tossed up, on off. Root defends it out.
Full  and on off, Root keeps it out.
On middle, tucked to mid-wikcet for a single.
On off, kept out.

A loud appeal for LBW turned down. Looped up, around off. Bairstow prods and looks to defend it out but misses. The ball come in contact with the pads. Ravindra Jadeja makes a appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Going down leg.
A length ball, on middle. Root flicks it through square leg for a single.
On a length, around off. Bairstow pushes it through cover for a couple of runs now.

OUT! CAUGHT! Mohammed Siraj strikes at the right time. And Jonny Bairstow has to walk back to the shed. Jonny Bairstow middles it, everyone thought it was going into the stands. Instead, it met the man in the deep Ravindra Jadeja. A short ball, on off. Bairstow rocks back and pulls it towards deep square leg. Everyone thought it was a six, as soon as he hit it. But it went straight to the man at deep square leg, where Ravindra Jadeja did not even move an inch and takes an easy catch. Mohammed Siraj shushes Jonny Bairstow on his way back.
Howout: c Ravindra Jadeja b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: A length ball, on off. Lawrence defends it out solidly.
Good length ball, outside off. Dan Lawrence leaves it alone.
On the pads, clipped to the leg side.
Full and on off. Root blocks it to the off side.
Floated full and on off. Root defends it out.
Darted on the pads. Root clips it to short fine leg for a single.
Play and a miss! Tossed up, outside off. Lawrence looks to go after it but misses.

EDGY! Full and on off. Lawrence looks to defend it out. The ball takes the outside edge and goes past the diving effort of Ajinkya Rahane at first slip. The ball rolls towards third man. They pick up a couple.
FOUR! Luckily, it goes through the man at square leg. Darted on the pads. Lawrence flicks it past square leg fielder. The ball ends up in the boundary.
Back-of-a-length ball, on off. Root defends it out watchfully.
A length ball, outside off. Root guides it towards short third man.
A full length ball, on middle. Root tucks it to the right of mid on for a single.
LEG BYE! A length ball, on the pads. Dan Lawrence looks to flick it away but misses. The ball clips the pads and goes towards fine leg. They collect a leg bye.
Siraj serves a back of a length ball, around off. Root stays back and guides it down to third man for a couple. The lead moves to 93 now.
A length ball, around off. Root defends it to cover.
Tossed up, on off. Dan Lawrence flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Flatter ball, on off. Dan Lawrence defends it.

Quikcer ball, around middle. Dan Lawrence defends it towards cover and looks to take a quick single. Virat Kohli collects the ball and throws it to the keeper. Rishabh Pant whips the bails off but he is well inside the crease as he dives.
Tossed up, on off. Dan Lawrence blocks it solidly.
Flatter ball, outside off. Dan Lawrence pushes it to cover.
Quicker ball on off. Dan Lawrence blocks it off the back foot.
Good length ball, on off. Joe Root pulls it towards deep mid-wicket and the ball falls just short of Ravindra Jadeja. They take one.
Length ball, on off, angling in. Driven towards mid off.
Good length ball, around off. Dan Lawrence pushes it to mid off.
Length ball, outside off. Dan Lawrence prods forward and gets an inside edge towards mid-wicket.
Full ball, on the pads. Dan Lawrence works it towards mid-wicket.
Full ball, outside off. Dan Lawrence leaves it alone.
Full ball, on off. Joe Root drags it to cover.
Tossed up, on off. Joe Root pushes it to cover.
Flighted ball, on off. Joe Root drives it towards sweeper cover for one.
Flighted ball, on off. Dan Lawrence steps down and defends it awkwardly.
Flatter ball, on off. Dan Lawrence rocks back to defend it.
FOUR! Short and wide. Dan Lawrence rocks back and cuts it through backward point for a boundary. The lead moves to 99 now.
A good length ball, outside off. Root taps it towards backward point for a single. That gets him into his 90s. Also, lead of 100 runs comes up for England.
A full length ball, on middle and leg. Dan Lawrence clips it to mid-wicket.

BEATEN! It's a great delivery by Mohammed Shami. A length ball, just outside the off pole. The ball stays straight after pitching. Dan Lawrence moves across and looks to defend it out but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
A full length ball, on off. Dan Lawrence looks to defend it out. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards the slip cordon.
FOUR! Runs keep on coming for Dan Lawrence. A full length ball, strayed on the pads. Lawrence flicks it towards deep sqaure leg for a boundary.
