A good looking drive this time! A full length ball, outside off. Lawrence creams it through covers. Cheteshwar Pujara gives it a chase and save a run for his team. The batters run three.
NO BALL! A good length ball, outside off. Lawrence shoulders his arms. The umpire signals a no ball, as he oversteps.
A length ball, on off. Lawrence flicks it through square leg for a couple.
A length ball, on off. Lawrence pushes it to cover.
A full length ball, on the pads. Lawrence clips it to the left of deep square leg. The batters pick a couple.
FOUR! This is a gift for Dan Lawrence. A length ball, drifting onto the pads. Lawrence clips it uppsihly through deep square leg for a boundary.

OUT! LBW! Good bowling by Shardul Thakur. He keeps this one straight and breaks through the defense of Dan Lawrence. Thakur gets his first wicket of this innings. He serves a length ball, around middle. The ball stays straight after pitching. Lawrence wanted to work it to the leg side but was very late into his shot. The ball goes onto come in contact with the pads. Thakur and company make an appeal and the umpire raises his finger in a flash. Dan Lawrence has a chat with the skipper, Joe Root and goes for the review. The Ball Tracker shows three reds and the review goes against England this time. They lose another wicket here and maybe the game is tilting back in the favour of India.
Howout: lbw b Shardul Thakur

Commentary: Good length ball, on off. Jos Buttler defends it off the back foot.
Good length ball, angling in. Joe Root turns it towards mid-wicket.
BYE! Good length ball, down leg. Joe Root misses the flick and keeper fails to collect the ball. They take one.
Good length ball, on off. Jos Buttler defends it off the back foot.
NO BALL! Length ball, on off. Jos Buttler blocks it off the back foot. Umpire signals a no ball due to overstepping.
FOUR! Length ball, strayed on the pads. Jos Buttler clips it towards square leg for a boundary.
Good length ball, on off. Jos Buttler blocks it watchfully off the back foot.
FOUR! Good length ball, around off. Jos Buttler punches it off the back foot through covers for a boundary.
Length ball, outside off. Joe Root leaves it alone.
Length ball, on middle. Joe Root clips it towards mid-wicket.
Good length ball, on off, angling in. Joe Root prods forward and blocks it.
Serves a length ball, on middle. Joe Root clips it towards square leg for one.
Full ball, outside off. Jos Buttler pushes it towards mid off.
Good length ball, outside off. Jos Buttler leaves it alone and lets it through to the keeper.
Good length ball, angling in. Joe Root rocks back to defend this one.
Length ball, around off. Joe Root taps it towards backward point.
Length ball, outside off. Joe Root taps it towards point for a quick single.
BEATEN! Good length ball, outside off. Jos Buttler pokes at it but misses as the ball nips away slightly.
FOUR! Full and wide. Jos Buttler drives it through covers for a boundary.
Good length ball, on off. Jos Buttler defends it off the back foot.
Good length ball, outside off. Joe Root defends it towards cover for a quick single.
Length ball, on off. Jos Buttler defends it off the back foot.

Good length ball, comes back in sharply. Jos Buttler leaves it alone and the ball hits on his pads. Shardul Thakur appeals but the umpire turns it down. The replays show that the ball would have gone over the stumps.
Length ball, outside off. Jos Buttler shoulders arms.
Length ball, on off. Jos Buttler defends it solidly towards cover.
Serves a length ball, on middle. Jos Buttler prods forward to defend it.
Length ball, comes back in sharply. Joe Root defends it towards mid-wicket.
Good length ball, around off. Joe Root taps it behind square on the off side for a couple of runs.
Length ball, on off. Joe Root works it towards sweeper cover for a run.
Good length ball, on off. Jos Buttler defends it towards cover.
NO BALL! Length ball, around off. Jos Buttler blocks it off the back foot but gets an outside edge towards third man for one.
Good length ball, on off. Jos Buttler pushes it towards mid off for a couple of runs.
Length ball, around off. Jos Buttler taps it towards point for a quick single. And the players will take Tea.
Good length ball, on off. Jos Buttler guides it through towards third man for a couple of runs.

OUT! BOWLED! OH NO! Jos Buttler has misjudged this one completely. Shardul Thakur gets his second wicket of the innings and he gets it in his first over, into the start of the final session. This is exactly what England did not want. The momentum is clearly shifting here. Good length ball, outside off, Jos Buttler shoulders his arms thinking the ball will hold its line. Instead, this one jags in a long way and disturbs the top of off stump. Shardul Thakur comes up with a beauty and get Buttler on his way back.
Howout: b Shardul Thakur

Commentary: Length ball, on off. Sam Curran pushes it to cover to get off the mark.
Good length ball, on off. Joe Root pushes it towards cover off the back foot.
Good length ball, around off. Joe Root taps it towards point.
Full ball, darted on the pads. Joe Root works it wide of the mid on fielder for a run.
Length ball, angling in slightly. Joe Root blocks it solidly.
Back-of-a-length ball, outside off. Joe Root pushes it to cover off the back foot.
BEATEN! Good length ball, outside off. Joe Root prods forward to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge as the ball nips way after pitching.
Good length ball, around middle. Joe Root defends it towards mid on.
Length ball, angling in. Joe Root pushes it uppishly towards mid on.

NOT OUT! Good length ball, came back in sharply and Joe Root is rapped on the pads as he tries to defend this one. Mohammed Siraj appeals but the umpire is unmoved. Siraj convinces the captain to take the review and they go up. The replays show that the impact was outside off. Joe Root survives. And India lose their review.
FOUR! Nicely played. Full and wide on off. Sam Curran creams it through covers for a boundary.
Length ball, around middle. Sam Curran defends it watchfully as the ball kept a bit low.
Good length ball, around off. Sam Curran taps it towards backward point for an easy run.
Length ball, outside off. The ball nipped back in after pitching and Joe Root is rapped on the pads. Shardul Thakur appeals but the umpire turns it down.
Full ball, outside off. Joe Root drives it back to the bowler.

Full ball, angling down leg. Joe Root misses the flick and the ball kisses his pads through to the keeper at his left. India appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Kohli jokingly asks Root, if it had clipped his pads, both of them share a smile.
BEATEN! SQUARED HIM UP! Good length ball, on off. Sam Curran looks to poke at it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length ball, on middle. Sam Curran works it on the leg side.

FOUR! PUNISHED! Short and wide. Sam Curran cuts in front of point and the ball races away to the boundary. Both the players throw some words at each other. This contest between Siraj and Curran is heating up.
banged in short, down leg. Sam Curran ducks under it and lets it through to the keeper.
Short ball, around shoulder high. Sam Curran taps it in front of the wicket. Mohammed Siraj is charged up and he has a word with Sam Curran.
Banged in short, outside off. Sam Curran ducks under it.

Short and wide. Joe Root cuts it towards cover and the ball falls just short of Cheteshwar Pujara there. Virat Kohli is in fun mood, as he sees the effort go short and is seen showing the "T" sign for the review. Just a reminder, India don't have a review left.
Full and wide. Joe Root drives it straight to the cover fielder.
Length ball, outside off. Joe Root looks to cut but misses as the ball stays low.
FOUR! There it is! Joe Root brings up his Hundred in style! Full and straight. Joe Root drives it straight back past the bowler for a boundary. The captain has certainly led from the front.
Good length ball, outside off. Joe Root stays back to cut but misses as the ball keeps low.
Lemgth ball, on middle and leg. Joe Root clips it towards deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Good length ball, outside off, left alone by Root.
Good length ball, around off. Joe Root taps it towards point for a quick run.
FOUR! Good length ball, down leg. Sam Curran tickles it towards fine leg for a boundary.
Length ball, around middle. Sam Curran pushes it towards mid on.
Short and just wide. Sam Curran cuts it towards deep point for a run.
Banged in short, outside off. Joe Root ducks under it.
Flatter ball, on off. Sam Curran pushes it hard to cover.
FOUR! NICELY TIMED! Quicker ball, on off. Sam Curran rocks back and punches it through covers for a boundary. The lead moves to 168 runs.
Flatter ball, on off. Sam Curran blocks it out watchfully.
Quicker and flatter on middle. Sam Curran defends it off the back foot.
Flatter ball, on off. Sam Curran pushes it back to the bowler.
Quicker ball, outside off. Sam Curran stays back and works it towards point for a run.
Good length ball, on off. Sam Curran defends it off the back foot.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Sam Curran turns it towards mid-wicket.
Full and wide. Sam Curran drives it through covers but Cheteshwar Pujara dives to stop the ball and saves a certain boundary.
Back of a length ball, on off. Curran ducks under it.
Good length ball, around off. Sam Curran taps it towards cover for a quick run.
Length ball, outside off. Joe Root comes forward and defends it towards cover. They scamper through for a single.
Tossed up, on off. Joe Root pushes it towards cover for a quick run.
Flatter ball, on middle. Sam Curran defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter ball, on off. Sam Curran works it down to long off for one.
Tossed up, around middle and leg.  Joe Root gets down on one knee and sweeps it to short fine leg.
Flatter ball, around off. Joe Root comes forward to defend this one.
Quicker ball, darted on the pads. Joe Root works it on the leg side for one.

Good length ball, angled in sharply and Joe Root is rapped on the pads in front. Mohammed Siraj appeals but the umpire turns it down. Virat Kohli tries to convince the umpire for the catch, if the ball took an inside edge. The replays roll in and show that the ball was missing the stumps this time as well. Also, India have no review left on them.
Good length ball, on off. Joe Root pushes it on the off side for a single.
Length ball, around off. Sam Curran works it towards point for a run.
Good length ball, on off. Joe Root defends it back to the bowler.
Full and wide. Joe Root drives it square on the off side for a run.
Banged in short, down leg. Sam Curran ducks under it and lets the ball go through to the keeepr.
A length ball, outside off. Root pushes it to cover.
Bumrah serves it on a length, outside off. Root taps it to the right of gully. They take a single.
A length ball, on the pads. Curran stays back and defends it out solidly.
A length ball, around off, coming across the left-hander. Curran stays back and pushes it through point for a single.
A full length ball, on off, Root defends it to the off side.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Jasprit Bumrah finds the outside edge. The new ball comes to the rescue of the Indian side. A fine innings of Joe Root finally comes to an end. Bumrah serves a length ball, outside off. There was a hint of an away movement. Root looks to defend it out. But only manages to get a thick outside edge. The ball flies to the right of Rishabh Pant behind the wickets. He takes an easy catch to depart the skipper. The crowd at Trent Bridge is on its feet, to applaud the effort of their skipper, Joe Root.
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary: Shami starts with a back of a length ball, on off. Curran ducks under it.
Good length ball, outside off. Curran leaves it alone.
Back of a length ball, outside off. Curran lets it sail past him.
A full length ball, on off. Curran drives it to cover for a single.
Back of a length ball, around off. Robinson guides it towards backward point. Ollie Robinson is off the mark on his first delivery. They take a couple.

FOUR! Ollie Robinson has surely come with an intent. A full length ball, on the pads. Ollie Robinson stays back and clips it through square leg. The ball races away to the boundary. Can he pull off a Bumrah for his team?
A length ball, on middle. Curran defends it back to the bowler.
BEAUTY! A length ball, around off, coming across the left-hander. Curran looks to defends it out, but pulls his bat back in time. The ball zips past the outside edge.
A length ball, outside off. Curran stays back and pushes it through covers. The batter pick up two comfortably.

DROPPED! ALMOST! Back of a length ball, around off. Curran guides it to the right of gully. Ajinkya Rahane dives to his right, but only manages to get fingertips on it. The ball goes towards third man and they pick two more.
BEATEN! A length ball, around off. Moving away. Curran looks to defend it out but misses. The ball beats the outside edge.
A length ball, on off. Curran gets squared up, as he blocks it out.
Play and a miss! On a length, outside off. Robinson looks to go after it but misses it completely.
A slower length ball, around off. Robinson guides it past gully. KL Rahul gives it a chase and cuts it off before the ropes. The batters pick three.
Innovative from Curran. A length ball, on off. Curran moves away and paddle scoops it over the keeper's head towards third man. The only get one, as there is a fielder present there.
FOUR! Ollie Robinson is on a roll here. A full length ball, outside off. Robinson pushes it through point. The ball races away to the boundary.
Back of a length ball, outside off. Robinson looks to chase it but misses.

Play and a miss! A length ball, around off. The ball nips away after pitching. Robinson looks to push it away but misses. The ball beats the outside edge. The movement was such, that it felt as if he had nicked it.
Bumrah serves a length ball, on off. Curran taps it to point.
In the air..Safe! A full length ball, on off. Curran looks to get under it. He lifts it over extra cover and the ball lands in a vacant area. The batters take two. The lead now moves to 200.
A length ball, on off. Curran defends it out solidly.

OUT! CAUGHT! Jasprit Bumrah picks up his fourth wicket and England are now 8 down. Bumrah fires in a quicker delivery. On a length, around off. Curran is cramped up for space. He looks to flick it to the leg side, but only manages to chip it towards mid on. Mohammed Siraj is placed there brilliantly. He takes an easy catch. The fiery contest between Siraj and Curran ends here. And, Siraj with that catch has the last laugh. England slip further.
Howout: c Mohammed Siraj b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary: OUT! TIMBER! Jasprit Bumrah is in a hurry to end things here. This is the Bumrah we knew. He his back with a bang in this Pataudi Series. Bumrah picks up two wickets in two deliveries, which also completes his 5-fer. Bumrah fires in a full length ball, on off. Board looks to dig it out but misses. The ball goes onto castle the stumps. Can Jasprit Bumrah wrap things up in the last ball of the over. Lets find out, he is on a Hat Trick.
Howout: b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary: NO BALL! Full ball, angling in from outside off. James Anderson blocks it out. Called no ball by the umpire as there were 3 fielders behind square on the leg side.
BEAUTY! Good length ball, angling away after pitching. James Anderson had no answers to this one. He is beaten of his outside edge.
Banged in short. Ollie Robinson swings hard but misses.
FIVE WIDES! Short ball, well down leg and too high. Rishabh Pant tries his best to catch it but it goes past him for a boundary. Handy runs these for England.
Good length ball, on off. Ollie Robinson pushes it towards cover for a couple of runs.
NASTY BOUNCER! Banged in short. Ollie Robinson swings hard but misses and he has been hit on the helmet here. The physio will be out to check on him.
Full ball, angling in on the pads. Ollie Robinson whips it towards fine leg.

OUT! CAUGHT! There is the last wicket that India badly wanted. And Mohammed Shami finally gets a wicket. Good length ball, on off. Ollie Robinson swings hard but gets a top edge and the ball goes straight to Ajinkya Rahane at third man. Excellent field placement from Virat Kohli there as Ajinkya did not have to move an inch to take this catch. England are bowled out for 303.
Howout: c Ajinkya Rahane b Mohammed Shami

Commentary: Full and outside off. KL Rahul defends it watchfully towards point.
Length ball, outside off. KL Rahul leaves it alone.
BEAUTY! Length ball, around off. KL Rahul pokes at it but is beaten past the outside edge as the ball nips away slightly after pitching.
Good length ball, outside off. KL Rahul looks to defend it off the back foot but is beaten all ends up.
Length ball, angling in slightly. KL Rahul comes forward and defends it watchfully.
Length ball, on the pads. KL Rahul whips it off his pads towards fine leg for a single. So India and KL Rahul are off the mark!
Good length ball, oustide off. KL Rahul prods forward but leaves it alone as there is some extra bounce on offer for Stuart Broad.
FOUR! CLASSY! Full and outside off. KL Rahul comes forward and drives it through the vacant cover region for a boundary.
Good length ball, on middle. KL Rahul defends it towards mid-wicket.
Length ball, outside off. KL Rahul shoulders arms to this one.
Short-of-a-length ball, outside off. KL Rahul looks to poke at it but pulls out late.
Good length ball, angling away. KL Rahul leaves it alone. Good testing areas from Stuart Broad.
Length ball, around off. Rohit Sharma comes forward to defend but gets an outside edge towards gully.
Length ball, on middle. Rohit Sharma watchfully defends it.
BEAUTY! Good length ball, around off. Rohit Sharma looks to defend but gets beaten past his outside edge as there is some outswing on offer.
Length ball, on middle. Rohit Sharma tucks it towards mid-wicket to get off the mark.
FOUR! NICELY DONE! Overpitched ball, on off. KL Rahul just pushes it off the front foot back past the bowler for a boundary.
Length ball, around off stump channel. KL Rahul defends it solidly.

A length ball, on the pads. Sharma looks to flick it away but it goes off the under edge and onto the pitch. KL Rahul says no starightaway for the run, while Sharma was searching for the ball. Rahul is certainly making sure he communicates this time around, unlike the last innings.
A full length ball, on off. Sharma tucks it to mid-wicket.
LEG BYE! A length ball, around the hips. Sharma hops and looks to flick it away but misses. The ball clips the thigh pad and goes towards fine leg. The batters collect a leg bye.
Back of a length ball, around off. Rahul sways away from the line of the delivery.
Good length ball, outside off. Rahul lets it go to the keeper.
A short ball, outside off. Rahul lets it go to the keeper. Broad surely kept things tight here.
Anderson sqaures up Sharma here. Anderson serves a length ball, on middle. Sharma looks to flick it to the leg side. The ball though takes the outside edge and goes towards point.
A full length ball, on off. Sharma tucks it to mid-wicket.
A length ball, around off. Sharma prods and defends it to cover.
A length ball, on off. Sharma goes back and defends it to the leg side.
Good leave by Sharma! A good length ball, outside off. Sharma shoulders his arms.
A full length ball, on off. Sharma pushes it to the right of the bowler. James Anderson dives to his right to make the stop. Good reflex.
A length ball, on off. Rahul tucks it to short leg.

Was it a leave or a miss! This is the new way Rahul leaves the delivery now a days. A length ball, just outside the off stump. Rahul looks to poke at it but pulls his bat back in time. A great delivery by Stuart Broad but a better leave by KL Rahul.
FOUR! STREAKY! A full length ball, around off. Rahul looks to defend it out. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards third man. The ball ends up in the boundary.
Back-of-a-length, outside off. Rahul leaves it alone.
Outside off, left alone by Rahul.
FOUR! Oh, what a shot! This shot is pleasing to your eyes. A full length ball, on off. Rahul drives it past mid off. The ball races away to the boundary. Exceptional batting.
A length ball, on off. Sharma pushes it to cover.

A full length ball, around off. The ball moves away after pitching. Sharma looks to defend it out. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to the left of gully. The man there dives to his left to make a good stop.
Back of a length ball, outside off. Sharma leaves it alone.
Good length ball, outside off. Sharma shoulders his arms.
A full length ball, on off. Sharma tucks it to square leg for a single.
Back-of-a-length ball, on middle. Rahul ducks under it.
In the air, but safe. Rohit Sharma looks to defend this good length ball but gets hit high on the bat and the ball just falls away from the gully fielder.
Length ball, angling in. KL Rahul pushes it to the leg side.
Good length ball, around off. KL Rahul gets behind the line and defends it solidly.
EXTRA BOUNCE! Good length ball, around off. KL Rahul gets behind the line of the ball and gets hit high on the bat. The ball lands safely.
Short of a length ball, around leg. KL Rahul tucks it awkwardly behind square on the leg side for one.
Length ball, angling in sharply, around middle and leg. Rohit Sharma works it towards fine leg for a run.
good length around middle. Rohit Sharma hops and tucks it towards fine leg for one.
Length ball, outside off. KL Rahul leaves it alone.
Good length ball, angling in slightly. KL Rahul defends it off the back foot.
Good length ball, way outside off. KL Rahul shoulders arms to this one.
FOUR! CLASSY! Full and wide. KL Rahul leans into this cover drive and the ball races away to the boundary line.
Length ball, around middle. KL Rahul defends it towards mid on watchfully.
Good length ball, on off. Rohit Sharma blocks it solidly towards point.
BEATEN! Good length ball, just around off. Rohit Sharma looks to play across the line and gets beaten past the outside edge as the ball holds its line.
Length ball, strayed on the pads. Rohit Sharma flicks it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Length ball, angling in, around off. KL Rahul defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! STREAKY! Good length ball, outside off. KL Rahul was in two minds whether to play or leave and gets a leading edge through the slip cordon for a boundary.
Length ball, coming in just that little bit. KL Rahul comes forward and blocks it solidly towards mid on. India are 33-0 after 10 overs.
Length ball, around middle. Rohit Sharma flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Full ball, outside off. Rohit Sharma blocks it solidly off the front foot.
Good length ball, on middle and leg. Rohit Sharma tucks it towards mid-wicket and scampers through for a run.
Length ball, outside off. KL Rahul prods forward and leaves it alone.

OUT! CAUGHT! And Stuart Broad provides the breakthrough for England. Good length ball, came in with the angle. KL Rahul looks to defend on the rise but gets an outside edge and the ball goes straight to Jos Buttler who makes no mistake. India lose their first wicket and a set batter has to depart. England are pumped up and they would look to get a couple more before stumps here.
Howout: c Jos Buttler b Stuart Broad

Commentary: A full length ball, on off. Pujara does what he does best. He defends it out watchfully.

NOT OUT! Rohit Sharma survives and England lose a crucial review, which could've come handy on Day 5. A good length ball, outside off. Sharma looks to poke it out but misses. The ball jags away off the pitch and it beats the outside edge. But wait a minute, Jos Buttler collects the ball and throws the ball up in the air in celebration. Seeing that, the crowd plays its part and makes an appeal on behalf of the team. During all this, Ollie Robinson did not look excited at all. He thought there was no nick, but seeing his team-mates jumping in the air, even he joined them. But still the umpire wasn't convinced. He shakes his head and says not out. Joe Root has a chat and takes it upstairs. The replays roll in and confirm there was no bat involved. A review goes in vain.
Length ball,around middle. Rohit Sharma flicks it towards mid-wicket for one.
BEATEN! Good length ball, around off. Cheteshwar Pujara looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge as it nips away slightly.
Length ball, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara leaves it late as there is some extra bounce for Ollie Robinson.
Length ball, angling in sharply. Cheteshwar Pujara turns it behind square on the leg side.
Good length ball, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara pushes it towards mid on off the back foot. Ollie Robinson keeping things tight here.
Good length ball, around middle. Rohit Sharma blocks it solidly.
Banged in short, around off. Rohit Sharma pulls it along the ground towards deep square leg for one.
FOUR! And Cheteshwar Pujara gets off the mark in some style. Full ball, on middle. Cheteshwar Pujara just chips it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Length ball, angling in. Cheteshwar Pujara pushes it towards mid on.
Good length ball, came back in sharply. Cheteshwar Pujara looks to flick it but gets an inside edge onto the pads. England appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
In the air, but safe. Cheteshwar Pujara looks to defend the incoming ball but gets an inside edge which falls just short of the square leg fielder. Cheteshwar Pujara survives.
Full ball, on middle. Rohit Sharma blocks it out.
Banged in short, around off. Rohit Sharma pulls it along the ground towards fine leg. Sam Curran dives to stop the boundary. They take a couple.
Good length ball, around middle. Rohit Sharma tucks it on the leg side for one.
Length ball, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara prods forward to defend and outside edges it towards slip on a bounce.

NO BALL! FOUR! Length ball, coming in sharply. Cheteshwar Pujara looks to defend it with soft hands and the ball beats the second slip fielder for a boundary. The umpire signals a no ball, as the bolwer oversteps.
Length ball, around middle. Cheteshwar Pujara pushes it off the front foot towards mid on.
FOUR! WOW! WHAT AN END TO THE DAY FOR India ! Ollie Robinson pitches it wide and full. Cheteshwar Pujara creams it through the vacant cover region for a boundary. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 4.
